Uses of Package
gov.loc.mets

  • Packages that use gov.loc.mets 
    Package Description
    gov.loc.mets  
  • Classes in gov.loc.mets used by gov.loc.mets 
    Class and Description
    AmdSecType
    amdSecType: Complex Type for Administrative Metadata Sections The administrative metadata section consists of four possible subsidiary sections: techMD (technical metadata for text/image/audio/video files), rightsMD (intellectual property rights metadata), sourceMD (analog/digital source metadata), and digiprovMD (digital provenance metadata, that is, the history of migrations/translations performed on a digital library object from it's original digital capture/encoding).
    AreaType
    areaType: Complex Type for Area Linking The area element provides for more sophisticated linking between a div element and content files representing that div, be they text, image, audio, or video files.
    BehaviorSecType
    behaviorSecType: Complex Type for Behavior Sections Behaviors are executable code which can be associated with parts of a METS object.
    BehaviorType
    behaviorType: Complex Type for Behaviors A behavior can be used to associate executable behaviors with content in the METS object.
    DivType
    divType: Complex Type for Divisions The METS standard represents a document structurally as a series of nested div elements, that is, as a hierarchy (e.g., a book, which is composed of chapters, which are composed of subchapters, which are composed of text).
    DivType.Fptr
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    DivType.Mptr
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    FileGrpType
    fileGrpType: Complex Type for File Groups The file group is used to cluster all of the digital files composing a digital library object in a hierarchical arrangement (fileGrp is recursively defined to enable the creation of the hierarchy).
    FileType
    fileType: Complex Type for Files The file element provides access to content files for a METS object.
    FileType.FContent
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    FileType.FContent.XmlData
    Java class for anonymous complex type.

    MdSecType
    mdSecType: Complex Type for Metadata Sections A generic framework for pointing to/including metadata within a METS document, a la Warwick Framework.
    MdSecType.MdRef
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MdSecType.MdWrap
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MdSecType.MdWrap.XmlData
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Mets
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MetsType
    metsType: Complex Type for METS Sections A METS document consists of seven possible subsidiary sections: metsHdr (METS document header), dmdSec (descriptive metadata section), amdSec (administrative metadata section), fileGrp (file inventory group), structLink (structural map linking), structMap (structural map) and behaviorSec (behaviors section).
    MetsType.FileSec
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MetsType.FileSec.FileGrp
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MetsType.MetsHdr
    Java class for anonymous complex type.

    Java class for anonymous complex type.

    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MetsType.MetsHdr.MetsDocumentID
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    MetsType.StructLink
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    ObjectType
    objectType: complexType for interfaceDef and mechanism elements The mechanism and behavior elements point to external objects--an interface definition object or an executable code object respectively--which together constitute a behavior that can be applied to one or more
    elements in a .
    ParType
    parType: Complex Type for Parallel Files The or parallel files element aggregates pointers to files, parts of files, and/or sequences of files or parts of files that must be played or displayed simultaneously to manifest a block of digital content represented by an element.
    SeqType
    seqType: Complex Type for Sequences of Files The seq element should be used to link a div to a set of content files when those files should be played/displayed sequentially to deliver content to a user.
    StructLinkType
    structLinkType: Complex Type for Structural Map Linking The Structural Map Linking section allows for the specification of hyperlinks between different components of a METS structure delineated in a structural map.
    StructLinkType.SmLink
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    StructLinkType.SmLinkGrp
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    StructLinkType.SmLinkGrp.SmArcLink
    The structMap arc link element is of xlink:type "arc" It can be used to establish a traversal link between two
    elements as identified by elements within the same smLinkGrp element.
    StructLinkType.SmLinkGrp.SmLocatorLink
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    StructMapType
    structMapType: Complex Type for Structural Maps The structural map (structMap) outlines a hierarchical structure for the original object being encoded, using a series of nested div elements.
